00:17:02,198 --> 00:17:03,331
-What did you say?

279
00:17:03,365 --> 00:17:05,198
-I have proof.

280
00:17:05,231 --> 00:17:07,431
Just take a look at
this photograph, huh?

281
00:17:10,765 --> 00:17:13,698
They have to make it here
by their own strength.

282
00:17:13,731 --> 00:17:15,831
Those are the
rules of this race.

283
00:17:15,865 --> 00:17:19,731
The boy must be disqualified.

284
00:17:19,765 --> 00:17:23,631
Which means that Fukusuke
Hikyakuya of the Wagarashi

285
00:17:23,665 --> 00:17:24,765
family is the winner.

286
00:17:24,798 --> 00:17:25,298
-What?

287
00:17:25,331 --> 00:17:26,665
It can't be!

288
00:17:26,698 --> 00:17:27,965
-But wait a minute.

289
00:17:27,998 --> 00:17:28,798
That was--

290
00:17:28,831 --> 00:17:30,798
-I'll hear none of your excuses.

291
00:17:30,831 --> 00:17:32,965
Jirocho, you gave your word.

292
00:17:32,998 --> 00:17:35,265
I want the Wasabi a family
to disband immediately.

293
00:17:37,798 --> 00:17:39,898
-Just a moment.

294
00:17:39,931 --> 00:17:41,698
There is no such rule.

295
00:17:41,731 --> 00:17:43,265
Stop talking nonsense.

296
00:17:43,298 --> 00:17:44,731
-But-- my lord!

297
00:17:44,765 --> 00:17:46,231
-But what?

298
00:17:46,265 --> 00:17:49,798
Are you suggesting I let
the Wagarashi win simply

299
00:17:49,831 --> 00:17:51,065
because you wish it?

300
00:17:51,098 --> 00:17:51,898
-No.

301
00:17:51,931 --> 00:17:53,165
Of course not.

302
00:17:53,198 --> 00:17:55,198
-Perhaps the reason you
want to win so badly

303
00:17:55,231 --> 00:17:57,398
is that it would mean an
end to all the bribes you've

304
00:17:57,431 --> 00:17:59,065
been accepting.

305
00:17:59,098 --> 00:18:01,931
Look here.

306
00:18:01,965 --> 00:18:03,631
You ignoramous.

307
00:18:03,665 --> 00:18:06,398
you'll give up your position
and don a monk's robe.

308
00:18:06,431 --> 00:18:09,098
-Yes-- Yes, sir.

309
00:18:09,131 --> 00:18:11,231
-And you, Kyuroku.

310
00:18:11,265 --> 00:18:12,431
-Yes?

311
00:18:12,465 --> 00:18:14,198
-I have heard a great
deal about the evil deeds

312
00:18:14,231 --> 00:18:15,498
you have committed.

313
00:18:15,531 --> 00:18:18,065
Your crimes against the
people of Port Degarashi

314
00:18:18,098 --> 00:18:19,598
are unforgivable.

315
00:18:19,631 --> 00:18:23,065
From this day forth, the
Wagarashi family is no more.

316
00:18:23,098 --> 00:18:24,065
Is that clear?

317
00:18:27,298 --> 00:18:28,398
-Yes, sir.

318
00:18:28,431 --> 00:18:29,698
[laughter]

319
00:18:29,731 --> 00:18:31,698
-An auspicious day.

320
00:18:31,731 --> 00:18:35,165
Now let us consider
this matter ended.

321
00:18:35,198 --> 00:18:38,431
[cheering]

322
00:18:41,398 --> 00:18:43,898
-I want to thank you for
all your help, Naruto.

323
00:18:43,931 --> 00:18:48,165
-Yeah, well, it was my pleasure.

324
00:18:48,198 --> 00:18:50,665
-I've come to get the wounded.

325
00:18:50,698 --> 00:18:52,931
-Ibiki-sensei.

326
00:18:52,965 --> 00:18:54,765
-Big brother!

327
00:18:54,798 --> 00:18:56,498
-Where is the wounded?

328
00:18:56,531 --> 00:18:58,531
-He's right over here.

329
00:18:58,565 --> 00:18:59,598
-OK.

330
00:18:59,631 --> 00:19:01,265
Let's get him on the boat, then.

331
00:19:01,298 --> 00:19:02,231
-Oh.

332
00:19:02,265 --> 00:19:04,398
Right.

333
00:19:04,431 --> 00:19:06,431
-Um, excuse me.

334
00:19:06,465 --> 00:19:09,131
-What is it?

335
00:19:09,165 --> 00:19:10,865
-Oh-- never mind.

336
00:19:14,265 --> 00:19:15,765
-Big brother.

337
00:19:15,798 --> 00:19:17,031
Big brother!

338
00:19:17,065 --> 00:19:17,731
Hold on!

339
00:19:20,398 --> 00:19:21,731
-Who are you?

340
00:19:21,765 --> 00:19:24,665
Only one person called me that.

341
00:19:24,698 --> 00:19:26,198
And he died three years ago.

342
00:19:35,331 --> 00:19:36,998
IDATE (VOICEOVER): Big brother.

343
00:19:37,031 --> 00:19:40,565
I've figured out the answer
to the 10th question.

344
00:19:40,598 --> 00:19:43,698
I'll never betray
a comrade again.

345
00:19:43,731 --> 00:19:46,165
I know what it means
now to trust in others.

346
00:19:54,665 --> 00:19:56,298
IBIKI (VOICEOVER):
You've grown up well.

347
00:20:06,731 --> 00:20:07,931
-So long, Idate!

348
00:20:07,965 --> 00:20:09,398
See you again someday!

349
00:20:09,431 --> 00:20:10,831
-Yeah, we'll see you.

350
00:20:10,865 --> 00:20:11,765
You take care.

351
00:20:11,798 --> 00:20:13,098
-You got it.

352
00:20:13,131 --> 00:20:14,965
You guys come back any time.

353
00:20:14,998 --> 00:20:17,298
-Hey boss, take care
of yourself, OK?

354
00:20:17,331 --> 00:20:19,765
-Yeah.

355
00:20:19,798 --> 00:20:21,431
-Buh bye!

356
00:20:21,465 --> 00:20:22,398
-So long!

357
00:20:26,265 --> 00:20:28,331
IBIKI (VOICEOVER): Always
interesting, this kid.

358
00:20:28,365 --> 00:20:32,831
It's no wonder the Fifth Hokage
has taken a shine to him.

359
00:20:32,865 --> 00:20:33,665
-Naruto!

360
00:20:33,698 --> 00:20:35,831
Thanks again!

361
00:20:35,865 --> 00:20:37,098
-Idate!

362
00:20:37,131 --> 00:20:40,531
Next time I see you, we'll
have to spar a little!

363
00:20:44,731 --> 00:20:45,398
-Sasuke.

364
00:20:45,431 --> 00:20:46,865
Does it hurt?

365
00:20:46,898 --> 00:20:48,065
-No, it doesn't.

366
00:20:48,098 --> 00:20:49,231
-Oh good.

367
00:20:49,265 --> 00:20:50,565
Don't worry.

368
00:20:50,598 --> 00:20:52,998
Those wounds will heal once
we get back to the village.

369
00:20:53,031 --> 00:20:53,498
-Sure.

370
00:20:56,331 --> 00:20:58,665
AOI (VOICEOVER): I see
that the stories are true.

371
00:20:58,698 --> 00:21:01,465
I'd always heard that the
last of the great Uchia clan

372
00:21:01,498 --> 00:21:05,098
was a hopeless loser
unworthy of his family name.

373
00:21:05,131 --> 00:21:08,265
SASUKE (VOICEOVER): I
wasn't able to beat him.

374
00:21:08,298 --> 00:21:12,331
But Naruto-- Naruto was.

375
00:21:30,292 --> 00:21:33,192
[theme music]

376
00:23:02,326 --> 00:23:03,959
SAKURA: Sasuke, Naruto.

377
00:23:03,992 --> 00:23:06,192
What's happened to both of you?

378
00:23:06,226 --> 00:23:06,859
Come on.

379
00:23:06,892 --> 00:23:08,959
This is a hospital.

380
00:23:08,992 --> 00:23:10,659
Sasuke's recouperating.

381
00:23:10,692 --> 00:23:12,859
You should know better, Naruto.

382
00:23:12,892 --> 00:23:15,692
Stop messing around already.

383
00:23:15,726 --> 00:23:16,759
Geez, what is this?

384
00:23:16,792 --> 00:23:18,192
Why is this happening?

385
00:23:21,559 --> 00:23:24,692
NARUTO: Next time,
The Battle Begins!

386
00:23:24,726 --> 00:23:25,559
Naruto Versus Sasuke!

